div.p:
1) Do SOVs agree or disagree that future negotiations can work out initial
                    measures as well as full treaty and that these initial measures could be put
                    into effect even before total program agreed;

2) SOVs referred to formulation in Indian resolution of November 15, 1960,
                    stating that if US prepared to work on both full treaty and initial measures
                    without prejudice to former, perhaps we could find common ground in pertinent
                    language contained in Indian resolution which could create basis for agreement;
                    wondered whether US could accept that language or perhaps whole resolution;
